title: Serialize/MacroDef-normalized
description: AST-only mode drops trailing spaces after the end marker
tags: $:/tags/wikitext-serialize-normalize-spec
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple

title: info

An `\end   ` marker decorated with trailing spaces becomes a bare `\end`.

Why: the AST records name, parameters and definition text; the end marker
line is reconstructed, so decoration on it disappears.

* Covers: $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/rules/macrodef.js.
* Mode: ast-only (the Input field withholds the source from the serializer).
+
title: Input
mode: ast-only

\define myMacro()
nothing
\end   

<<myMacro>>
+
title: ExpectedWikitext

\define myMacro()
nothing
\end

<<myMacro>>
